Package org.ietf.nea.pa.validate.rules

IETF integrity measurement validation rules.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AssessmentResult
    Rule, that checks if the assessment result ID is known.
    CommonLengthLimits
    Rule, that checks if a given length value is within common limits.
    FactoryDefaultPasswordStatus
    Rule, that checks if factory default password status ID is known.
    ForwardingStatus
    Rule, that checks if traffic forwarding status ID is known.
    LastUseSyntaxCheck
    Rule, that Checks if the syntax of the date for an operation's last us is valid.
    MessageVersion
    Rule, that checks if the message version is supported.
    MinAttributeLength
    Rule, that checks if the given length satisfies the minimum attribute length requirement.
    MinEntryCount
    Rule, that checks if the given list contains a minimal amount of entries.
    NoNullTerminatedString
    Rule, that checks if string is not terminated with null.
    NoSkipOnUnknownAttribute
    Rule, that checks if no skip flag is set in the set of flags.
    NoZeroString
    Rule, that checks if string contains zero characters.
    OpposingPortFilterEntries
    Rule, that checks if the list contains valid port filter entries.
    PaAttributeNoSkip
    Rule, that checks if an attribute needs a no skip flag and the no skip flag is contained in the set of lags.
    ProductInformationZeroConstraint
    Rule, that checks if product ID is zero if vendor ID is zero.
    RequestingForbiddenAttributes
    Rule, that checks if the list of attribute references contains references to forbidden attributes.
    StringLengthLimit
    Rule, that checks if a string is to large.
    TypeReservedAndLimits
    Rule, that checks if the attribute type ID is reserved or not in range.
    UriSyntax
    Rule, that checks if an URI string has a valid syntax.
    VendorIdReservedAndLimits
    Rule, that checks if the attribute vendor ID is reserved or not in range.
